OL,3,CTeenage boy and woman sentenced after
OL,4,C'luring' pensioner to his death
OL,6,F"Telling my family, friends, and work
OL,7,Fcolleagues that my dad had been
OL,8,Fmurdered was surreal and devastating.
OL,10,F"The words feeling foreign when they
OL,11,Fleft my mouth. It is still difficult
OL,12,Fnow to say the words out loud.
OL,14,F"Prior to all of this my dad was a
OL,15,Fkind man, generous and hardworking, he
OL,16,Floved to laugh and had many friends."
OL,18,FDetective Inspector Jim Colclough,
OL,19,Ffrom , said: "It was a tragic case of
OL,20,Fa vulnerable man being killed by
OL,21,Fpeople he thought he could trust.
